Description: Geoffrey Byruch LLC applies creative thinking and strategy in the field of entrepreneurship and investment banking.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Geoffrey Byruch is a New Yorker-based entrepreneur who is always on the hunt for new and exciting opportunities. At a young age, he was always attuned to the world of business and knew that in order to succeed he had to set himself apart from his competition. Whether it was spending his winters shoveling his neighbors’ driveways or his college days shaking hands and signing contracts for new business opportunities, Geoffrey knew that his time, effort, and dedication will lead him to his one goal, success. For small businesses and entrepreneurs, Geoffrey’s advice from them, besides the already repetitive logistical business and leadership tactics that entrepreneurship books sells, is to have passion. Passion, in Geoffrey’s world, is the real drive for success. It is an innate fuel that gives you the stamina day-in and day-out. Whether times are good or times are challenging, passion is what will allow a person for their everlasting long-term goal. This is ultimately the definer for success and failure. If you want to be successful, follow Geoffrey’s mentality and allow your passion to steal the show. Today, Geoffrey Byruch has entered the world of entrepreneurship and is seeking new and exciting ventures to invest and create for his future. While he may not be the only entrepreneur in the world, Geoffrey uses his vision, adaptability, and personality to drive him to his goals each and every day. He uses the hope for success rather than the trepidation for failure as his huge motivator in accomplishing his objectives and hitting his targets. It is that mentality and positive intrinsic belief that allowed Geoffrey to see success within a multitude of industries. Even when it came to undertakings different and difficult projects, Geoffrey Byruch made sure to adapt for success in every aspect of any business that he was apart of. For him, it didn’t matter if he was playing the face of the business or behind the scenes; Geoffrey’s adamant belief in learning, understanding, and perfecting every trade was critical for success. He believed that, in order to evolve as a businessman, he needed to know everything from the ground up. This sense of modesty, humility, and openness allowed him to gain the vital skills to evolve in the business world. Using his past experiences as a child to his life work in the business world, Geoffrey was able to attain a variety of success such as holding his Series 7, 24, 55, 63, and 79 licenses, establishing long everlasting partnerships, and creating and succeeding in a variety of small businesses. When Geoffrey is not in the office or working on building a new business, he likes to relax with his family and friends. Geoffrey Byruch is, first and foremost, a family man. As a loving husband and proud father of three, Geoffrey loves to spend his quality leisure time with them as much as possible. When he is not with them, you can usually find Geoffrey with his friends cheering on the Philadelphia Eagles. Some of Geoffrey Byruch's interests include wine, good food, New York City restaurants, Cuban cigars, sports (football, baseball, and basketball), and anything related to Philadelphia.

Description: Centripetal Software provides solutions for users to back up data and files stored in online applications.

Our first product provides the most comprehensive backup solution on the market for business users of 37Signals Basecamp product. Their Application Data Retrieval service is itself an online, hosted application used to perform a complete retrieval of your files, application data, or application database on hosted business applications. The retrieval software enables you to make an exact duplicate of everything contained within supported online applications so that you are in control of the data that you own.  Centripetal Software gives companies the power of Cloud Applications with the control that comes with owning the desktop. Their products allow you to keep your data by retrieving it from the online applications that you use and storing it how you want it stored. They go a step further by enabling you to migrate that data to competing products giving you a choice and limiting vendor lock in. Their vision is to extend core IT services into the cloud so that companies can continue to manage their IT even as they move to online applications. Everyone else out there is focusing on making IT services themselves available in the cloud, but very few people are extending those IT services to work with cloud applications.

The Gulf of Maine is considered by many to offer great potential for wind energy. The state is also the home of the University of Maine currently undertaking the nation's first deepwater turbine construction under a grant from the US Department of Energy (DOE).
